00:42:49,817 --> 00:42:55,031
it’s now cheaper than coal,
oil and gas and will soon be much cheaper.

625
00:42:57,033 --> 00:43:01,099
Even without climate change, we would still
be moving away from fossil fuels simply because

626
00:43:01,099 --> 00:43:04,040
we have better, cleaner technology now.


627
00:43:04,249 --> 00:43:08,981
Electric cars are about to get much
cheaper, than traditional cars too and they are much

628
00:43:08,981 --> 00:43:12,006
more fun to drive.


629
00:43:12,560 --> 00:43:17,180
Of course, the stuff that goes into wind and
solar panels and electric cars still has to be dug

630
00:43:17,180 --> 00:43:21,059
from the ground, like oil and gas
- so it’s not perfect.

631
00:43:21,059 --> 00:43:25,150
But it’s still key to stop warming
the planet and give us a liveable future.

632
00:43:25,150 --> 00:43:31,442
It’s also important to remember that
renewable energy is just a technology, not a silver bullet.

633
00:43:31,550 --> 00:43:36,820
There’s a risk we fall into the old story
- create ever more demand to make ever more

634
00:43:36,820 --> 00:43:40,034
profits, and destroy
ecosystems along the way.

635
00:43:41,430 --> 00:43:45,530
We need to be efficient about the resources
we use, and not simply go crazy digging up

636
00:43:45,530 --> 00:43:48,569
all the lithium in the
world just because we can.

637
00:43:49,043 --> 00:43:53,423
Let’s only put up the solar panels
and wind turbines we need, not more.

638
00:43:54,424 --> 00:43:58,011
And let’s use them to benefit our communities.


639
00:43:58,011 --> 00:44:03,119
Because with renewables, we can produce
energy on our roofs, store it in batteries, and create

640
00:44:03,119 --> 00:44:05,290
micro-grids with the neighbors.


641
00:44:05,852 --> 00:44:10,023
The money stays in the local
economy, and we become more self-reliant.

642
00:44:12,025 --> 00:44:15,028
Oil and gas created good jobs for many years,


643
00:44:15,028 --> 00:44:18,656
but renewables will create a whole lot more of them!


644
00:44:19,032 --> 00:44:24,480
Already now, solar panel installer and wind
turbine technician are among the fastest growing

645
00:44:24,480 --> 00:44:26,039
job categories.


646
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:30,900
And we’ll need plenty of people to install
batteries, heat pumps, and car charging stations.

647
00:44:30,900 --> 00:44:36,170
We’ll see lots of work return to
local communities that had been bleeding jobs.

648
00:44:37,633 --> 00:44:39,300
Let’s zoom out.


649
00:44:39,300 --> 00:44:46,020
Everywhere, in food, in consumption,
production energy and other areas too, a new story,

650
00:44:46,020 --> 00:44:49,079
a better story is emerging and gaining steam.


651
00:44:49,079 --> 00:44:51,109
And sometimes rapidly.


652
00:44:51,109 --> 00:44:54,710
But the million dollar question is:
can this be enough?

653
00:44:54,710 --> 00:44:59,600
Let’s assume we do all this,
can we turn the ship around?

654
00:45:00,448 --> 00:45:06,970
In 2014, a group of 200 scientists and
specialists put together a list of all the big ideas on

655
00:45:06,970 --> 00:45:09,690
how to stop climate breakdown.


656
00:45:09,690 --> 00:45:13,290
They mainly focused on carbon,
but many of their solutions also provide breakthroughs

657
00:45:13,290 --> 00:45:17,430
in stabilizing ecosystems and reducing pollution.


658
00:45:17,430 --> 00:45:21,010
This effort is called "Project Drawdown".


659
00:45:21,220 --> 00:45:25,200
They came up with a list of 80 items -
with things we’ve talked about like upgrading

660
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:30,019
the way we grow food, replanting
forests, and switching to renewable energy.

661
00:45:30,019 --> 00:45:33,160
But also other things,
some of them quite surprising.

662
00:45:33,160 --> 00:45:37,450
For example recycling greenhouse gasses
in air conditioning units, which turns out to

663
00:45:37,450 --> 00:45:38,559
be a big deal.


