00:45:38,559 --> 00:45:43,460
They asked the question: What happens
if we were to take all our existing solutions and

665
00:45:43,460 --> 00:45:48,300
scale them up… would this be
enough to stop the world from getting too warm?

666
00:45:48,300 --> 00:45:51,690
Or do we fall short? The answer is…


667
00:45:51,690 --> 00:45:57,670
Yes, it could be enough, if we manage
to implement all the major solutions we have at hand.

668
00:45:57,670 --> 00:46:01,970
Actually, once we get to a point where we
stop the warming, in principle, we could even

669
00:46:01,970 --> 00:46:03,710
go into reverse.


670
00:46:03,710 --> 00:46:07,640
We could draw carbon back down from the
atmosphere and turn the thermostat back down.

671
00:46:08,432 --> 00:46:12,019
